# ── Cloudflare Pages redirect rules for frontierprotocol.app ─────────────────
#
# /nft/metadata/* is served by the Express backend (server/routes.ts), not by
# the static Vite build. Plot NFT ASAs carry a URL of the form
#   https://frontierprotocol.app/nft/metadata/<plotId>#arc3
# (see server/services/chain/land.ts:54), so wallets and indexers resolve the
# branded-domain URL — which used to fall through to the SPA shell because
# nothing in client/public/ claimed the path.
#
# PR #260 added external-origin 200 proxy rules to this file. Those rules are
# UNSUPPORTED by Cloudflare Pages: `_redirects` only accepts `200` rewrites
# whose destination is a relative same-site URL, so the absolute Fly URLs
# were silently ignored at the edge and the SPA fallback below still served
# the Vite index.html.
#
# The supported mechanism is now a Pages Function — see
#   client/functions/nft/metadata/[[path]].ts
# which is scoped to /nft/metadata/* only by client/public/_routes.json.
# This file therefore retains only the catch-all SPA fallback, listed LAST
# so it never shadows a static asset (Pages prefers a real file on disk
# over a `_redirects` rule for any URL that resolves on the CDN).
#
# Static Vite build still owns:
#   /nft/biomes/*        → static PNG/SVG biome art (client/public/nft/biomes/)
#   /assets/*, /images/*, /textures/*, /story/*, /favicon.png, /robots.txt,
#     /sitemap.xml, /globe-rebuild-preview.html
#   and every SPA route (/*) → index.html (the SPA fallback below)
#
# Non-goals:
#   - does not change NFT URL construction in server/services/chain/* (URLs
#     stay on frontierprotocol.app — that's what minted ASAs already point at).
#   - does not change the Express route or the server build.
#   - does not touch /api/* (the client bundles VITE_API_URL to Fly directly).
#   - does not touch /nft/biomes/* (static assets remain on the CDN; also
#     explicitly excluded from the Pages Function in _routes.json).
#   - does not introduce an external-origin `_redirects` rule (unsupported —
#     see the comment above).

# SPA fallback — deep client routes (wouter) get the index.html shell. Listed
# last on purpose: Pages tries static assets first, then the Pages Function
# (per _routes.json include), and only then this rewrite.
/*                                  /index.html                                                         200
